x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The uncertainty in the yields is either
statistical, due to the number of gamma-ray counts,
or set to 7% due to uncertainties in the beam
integration, target location, and detector efficiency,
whichever is larger. This 7% figure is due to an
uncertainty of approximately 5% in bombardment
parameters such as current integration and 5% in
counting due to source location, and so forth. These
uncertainties are then added quadratically.
Bombardment parameters.
Source location.
Table II, page 346.

uncertainties are then added quadratically.

x4freetext: The quantity of interest in calculating thermonuclear
reaction rates for astrophysical purposes is the
product of Avogadro`s number with the average value
of the cross section times velocity, averaged over a

yields to form the product integral cross section
velocity over the Maxwellian distribution, the rates
are quoted over those temperature ranges for which
total errors do not exceed 100%.
